# 🔹 What is a Linked List?

A Linked List is a **dynamic linear data structure** where elements are stored in nodes.

Each node contains:

1. Data
2. Address of next node

Structure:

```c
struct Node
{
    int data;
    struct Node *next;
};
```

---

## Linked List vs Array

| Array             | Linked List           |
| ----------------- | --------------------- |
| Fixed size        | Dynamic size          |
| Contiguous memory | Non-contiguous memory |
| Fast indexing     | Sequential access     |
| Insertion costly  | Insertion easy        |

📌 Very common GATE comparison.

---

# 🔹 Singly Linked List (SLL)

Each node points to next node.

```text
10 → 20 → 30 → NULL
```

---

## Node Structure

```c
struct Node
{
    int data;
    struct Node *next;
};
```

---

## Operations

### Insertion at Beginning

```text
Before:
20 → 30

After:
10 → 20 → 30
```

Time Complexity:

[
O(1)
]

---

### Insertion at End

Need traversal.

Time Complexity:

[
O(n)
]

---

### Deletion at Beginning

Remove first node.

Time Complexity:

[
O(1)
]

---

### Search

Traverse node by node.

Time Complexity:

[
O(n)
]

---

# 🔹 Doubly Linked List (DLL)

Each node contains:

* Previous pointer
* Next pointer

Structure:

```c
struct Node
{
   int data;
   struct Node *prev;
   struct Node *next;
};
```

---

Representation:

```text
NULL ← 10 ⇄ 20 ⇄ 30 → NULL
```

---

## Advantages

✅ Forward traversal

✅ Backward traversal

✅ Easy deletion

---

## Disadvantages

❌ Extra memory for prev pointer

---

# 🔹 Circular Linked List (CLL)

Last node points back to first node.

```text
10 → 20 → 30
↑         ↓
└─────────┘
```

---

## Important Property

No NULL pointer exists.

---

## Applications

* CPU Scheduling
* Round Robin Scheduling
* Multiplayer Games

📌 Frequently asked in GATE.

---

# 🔹 Header Node

Special node at beginning.

Stores metadata like:

* Node count
* Start pointer

---

# 🔹 Traversal

For Singly Linked List:

```c
temp = head;

while(temp != NULL)
{
    temp = temp->next;
}
```

Time Complexity:

[
O(n)
]

---

# 🔹 Time Complexity Table

| Operation        | SLL  |
| ---------------- | ---- |
| Access           | O(n) |
| Search           | O(n) |
| Insert Beginning | O(1) |
| Delete Beginning | O(1) |
| Insert End       | O(n) |

---

# 🔹 Common GATE Traps

### Trap 1

Linked list does NOT support direct indexing.

❌

```c
list[5]
```

Impossible.

---

### Trap 2

Searching is NOT O(1).

It is:

[
O(n)
]

---

### Trap 3

DLL uses extra memory.

---

### Trap 4

Circular linked list has no NULL node.

